Beiersdorf’s New CEO Will Earn More, Manager Magazin Says

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-10-20T09:41:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/beiersdorf-s-new-ceo-will-earn-more-manager-magazin-says.html
Beiersdorf AG (BEI) ’s designated chief
executive officer, Stefan Heidenreich, will earn more than
departing CEO Thomas Quaas, Manager Magazin reported, citing
unidentified people within the company.  Heidenreich will earn about 3 million euros ($4.1 million)
a year compared to 1.1 million euros for Quaas, Manager Magazin
said, citing the people.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
